        <div class="authors">
            <a href="#">Chen, Wei</a><sup>1</sup>, <a href="#">Rodriguez, Maria</a><sup>2</sup>, <a href="#">Kumar, Ananya</a><sup>3</sup>, <a href="#">Thompson, James</a><sup>1</sup>, <a href="#">Nakamura, Yuki</a><sup>4</sup>, <a href="#">Schmidt, Hans-Peter</a><sup>5</sup>, <a href="#">O'Brien, Fiona</a><sup>2</sup>, <a href="#">Singh, Priya</a><sup>3</sup>, <a href="#">Williams, David</a><sup>1</sup>, <a href="#">Kim, Soo-Min</a><sup>6</sup>, <a href="#">Andersen, Erik</a><sup>5</sup>, <a href="#">Patel, Raj</a><sup>3</sup>, <a href="#">Murphy, Grace</a><sup>2</sup>, <a href="#">Fitzgerald, Thomas</a><sup>7</sup>, <a href="#">Johannsen, Lars</a><sup>5</sup>, <a href="#">Aziz, Omar</a><sup>8</sup>, <a href="#">Russo, Giuseppe</a><sup>9</sup>, <a href="#">Okonkwo, Chidi</a><sup>10</sup>, <a href="#">Kowalski, Tomasz</a><sup>11</sup>
        </div>
        
        <div class="affiliations">
            <sup>1</sup>MIT &nbsp; <sup>2</sup>Stanford University &nbsp; <sup>3</sup>Oxford &nbsp; <sup>4</sup>University of Tokyo &nbsp; <sup>5</sup>ETH Zurich &nbsp; <sup>6</sup>Tsinghua University &nbsp; <sup>7</sup>Imperial College London &nbsp; <sup>8</sup>University of Cambridge &nbsp; <sup>9</sup>University of Bologna &nbsp; <sup>10</sup>University of Lagos &nbsp; <sup>11</sup>University of Warsaw
        </div>
        
        <div class="doi">
            <a href="#">doi: 10.1234/arxiv.2024.0892345</a>
            <a href="#">DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/s00134-024-07891-x</a>
            <a href="#">https://doi.org/10.1038/s41586-023-04567-2</a>
        </div>
        
        <div class="abstract">
            <h2>Abstract</h2>
            <p>This survey presents a comprehensive overview of attention mechanisms in deep neural networks, covering their theoretical foundations, architectural variants, and applications across natural language processing, computer vision, and speech recognition. We examine the evolution from early attention mechanisms in sequence-to-sequence models to the revolutionary transformer architecture and its numerous variants. The survey includes detailed discussions of computational complexity, attention visualization techniques, and practical considerations for deployment. We also identify open research challenges and future directions in attention-based deep learning.</p>
        </div>
        
